'''突觸素'''（Synaptophysin），又稱'''主要突觸小泡蛋白p38'''（major synaptic vesicle protein p38），是一種人體中由「''SYP''」[[基因|基因]]轉譯而成的蛋白質<ref name="entrez">{{cite web | title = Entrez Gene: SYP synaptophysin| url = https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/entrez?Db=gene&Cmd=ShowDetailView&TermToSearch=6855}}</ref><ref name="pmid3120152">{{cite journal | vauthors = Südhof TC, Lottspeich F, Greengard P, Mehl E, Jahn R | title = The cDNA and derived amino acid sequences for rat and human synaptophysin | journal = Nucleic Acids Res. | volume = 15 | issue = 22 | pages = 9607 | date = November 1987 | pmid = 3120152 | pmc = 306499 | doi = 10.1093/nar/15.22.9607 }}</ref>。

== 遺傳學 ==
該基因位於[[X染色體|X染色體]]的短臂上（Xp11.23-p11.22），約由12,406個鹼基對所構成，位於反義股上。該蛋白由313個胺基所構成，分子量約為33.845[[原子质量单位|kDa]]。

== 分子生物學 ==
該蛋白質為[[突触小泡|突触小泡]]上的[[醣蛋白|醣蛋白]]，擁有四個穿膜區。該蛋白主要表現於[[內分泌系統|神經內分泌細胞]]，基本上只要擁有突觸傳輸功能的[[神經元|神經元]]皆會表達。在免疫染色組織學上，該蛋白常被作為神經內分泌腫瘤的標誌蛋白，或是用於突觸豐度的定量<ref name="pmid9023727">{{cite journal | vauthors = Calhoun ME, {{tsl|en|Mathias Jucker (neuroscientist) || Jucker M}}, Martin LJ, Thinakaran G, Price DL, Mouton PR | title = Comparative evaluation of synaptophysin-based methods for quantification of synapses | journal = J. Neurocytol. | volume = 25 | issue = 12 | pages = 821–8 | date = December 1996 | pmid = 9023727 | doi = 10.1007/BF02284844 }}</ref>。

目前該蛋白的確切功能尚未闡明，僅知他會與重要的突觸蛋白{{tsl|en|synaptobrevin|synaptobrevin}}產生交互作用。但在動物實驗中，即使將突觸素的基因敲除，似乎並沒有對動物的發育或功能上產生任何影響<ref name="pmid8643476">{{cite journal | vauthors = McMahon HT, Bolshakov VY, Janz R, Hammer RE, Siegelbaum SA, Südhof TC | title = Synaptophysin, a major synaptic vesicle protein, is not essential for neurotransmitter release | journal = Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U.S.A. | volume = 93 | issue = 10 | pages = 4760–4 | date = May 1996 | pmid = 8643476 | pmc = 39352 | doi = 10.1073/pnas.93.10.4760 | bibcode = 1996PNAS...93.4760M }}</ref>。近期研究顯示，突觸素的缺失可能導致小鼠出現行為異常，例如探索行為增加、新奇物辨識（object novelty recognition），以及空間感上產生影響<ref name="pmid19393300">{{cite journal | vauthors = Schmitt U, Tanimoto N, Seeliger M, Schaeffel F, Leube RE | title = Detection of behavioral alterations and learning deficits in mice lacking synaptophysin | journal = Neuroscience | volume = 162 | issue = 2 | pages = 234–43 | date = August 2009 | pmid = 19393300 | doi = 10.1016/j.neuroscience.2009.04.046 | citeseerx = 10.1.1.320.5309 }}</ref>。

